<!--
    Wikipedia W wordmark — direct port of the SVG path used on desktop
    (Simple Icons family, 0..24 viewBox).

    The same path string renders correctly through ResolverIcon.kt's
    parseSvgPath for ~every other icon, but the Wikipedia W ends up
    with a malformed bottom-left V vertex on Android. Tried fixing the
    `s` after non-curve case in parseSvgPath (the path uses
    `l-2.388 4.786 2.715 5.455s3.767-7.894 4.916-10.442`) — that's a
    real SVG-spec gap in our parser and was worth fixing on principle,
    but it didn't actually move the visible W rendering. Likely there's
    a second bug in either parseSvgPath or Compose's PathBuilder that
    only shows up in combination with the path's specific geometry.

    Rather than continue chasing the parser, special-case Wikipedia
    through Android's well-tested VectorDrawable parser. Same escape
    hatch SoundCloud (PNG) and Achordion (multi-color VectorDrawable)
    already use.
-->
